b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Chatfuel is best suited for social media businesses, e commerce, marketing teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Freshdesk (Freddy AI), meanwhile, shines for growing businesses, IT service desks, support teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2015, Chatfuel describes itself as \"No-code chatbot platform for Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp automation.\" Freshdesk (Freddy AI), established in 2010, positions itself as \"Customer support platform with Freddy AI for automated ticket resolution.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Freshdesk (Freddy AI)** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Chatfuel is a poor choice — far from it. Chatfuel excels in its own right, particularly for social media businesses and e commerce.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value good free plan for small teams, go with Freshdesk (Freddy AI). If easy no-code bot builder matters more to you, Chatfuel is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
